    <body>Select the <b class="Bold">Application</b> checkbox to provide group access to the Application activity.  When this checkbox is cleared, the option for creating a New Business Application is not shown in the New Activity drop-down list in FireLight. For example, clear this checkbox and select the Enable Create Needs Determination checkbox to force users to create a Needs Determination first and then use the Apply functionality from the Needs Determination Questionnaire or from the All Activities page to create the new business application. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Features/Application Activity.htm" target="_blank" alt="Application Activity">Application Activity</MadCap:xref> in Features<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online">. See also <MadCap:xref href="../../../../UserGuide/New Activity/Application.htm" target="_blank" alt="Application [User Instructions]">Application [User Instructions]</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></body>
</html>